OL,7,FThe IMF still characterises the UK's
OL,8,Flong-term prospects as "subdued" and
OL,9,Fthere are plenty of economic issues
OL,10,F(like a rise in economic inactivity)
OL,11,Fthat need tackling, but not so long
OL,12,Fago the idea that inflation could be
OL,13,Fbrought under control without a
OL,14,Fsignificant recession or a sharp rise
OL,15,Fin unemployment seemed unlikely.
OL,17,FSoft landings are preferable to hard
OL,18,Flandings but here's the hitch.
