OL,4,Cand warns post-election tax rises are
OL,5,Clikely
OL,7,FThe result: the IMF calculates that
OL,8,Fwhoever forms the next government will
OL,9,Fprobably need to achieve a fiscal
OL,10,Fconsolidation of 1% of GDP to prevent
OL,11,Fdebt rising during the next parliament.
OL,13,FPut another way: the next government
OL,14,Fwill have to either raise taxes or
OL,15,Freduce spending by around #30 billion
OL,16,Fa year at some point.
OL,18,FThis is a very large number. Reversing
OL,19,Fthe two National Insurance we've had
OL,20,Fsince last November would raise c#20
OL,21,Fbillion a year so wouldn't be enough.
