OL,4,Cand warns post-election tax rises are
OL,5,Clikely
OL,7,FThe IMF suggests an alternative
OL,8,Fsolution. The next government might
OL,9,Fdecide to restrict the services the
OL,10,Fstate provides.
OL,12,FOne idea it floats is the "expanded
OL,13,Fuse of charges for public services".
OL,14,FThe IMF doesn't elaborate but most
OL,15,Fworking-age adults in England pay for
OL,16,Ftheir prescriptions, for dentistry and
OL,17,Foptometry. Charges could be extended
OL,18,Fto cover GP appointments, for example.
