OL,7,FPolitical decisions need to be made
OL,8,Fabout what the size of the state
OL,9,Fshould be, what services the
OL,10,Fgovernment should provide and how
OL,11,Fthose services can be adequately
OL,12,Ffunded.
OL,14,FAs ever, the IMF's language is careful
OL,15,Fand caveated. The aim appears to be to
OL,16,Fimprove the public debate (and with it
OL,17,Fpublic policy) without causing the
OL,18,Fgovernment of the day any
OL,19,Fembarrassment.
